  "narrative_arc": "Starving ex-student in a coffin-sized garret who murders a pawnbroker. Dostoevsky documents his poverty with sensory detail — the stench of the stairwell, the heat of a St. Petersburg summer, the delirium of hunger. His confession isn't guilt but exhaustion — every system he touches demands performance he cannot sustain.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "Raskolnikov's dome maps the interior architecture of poverty-driven crime. His Layer 5 (Housing — the coffin room) and Layer 4 (Health — the fevers) are precisely documented. His dome tests whether circumstance explanations hold up when measured against real systems.",
